(4,'VARIABLES IN PHP','VARIABLES: created by $ sign\r\n	$myNameIs=\"Rizwan\";\r\n	echo \"I love $myNameIs!\";\r\n	echo \"I love \".$myNameIs.\"!\";\r\n\r\n1.Strings+int results strings:\r\nPHP is a Loosely Typed Language so we can add string and integer. use Strict mood to avoid this\r\n\r\n2.Global scope variables:\r\nA variable declared outside a function has a GLOBAL SCOPE and can only be accessed outside a function: To access inside function use global $IWasoutsider;\r\n\r\n3.Local scope variables\r\nA variable declared within a function has a LOCAL SCOPE and can only be accessed within that function:Once function is executed all local variables are deleted.\r\n\r\n4.How to access global variable inside functions:\r\nThe global keyword is used to access a global variable from within a function.\r\nie\r\n	$x = 5;\r\n	function myTest() {\r\n	    global $x;\r\n	    $x = $x + 5; //or $GLOBAL[\'x\']=$GLOBAL[\'x\']+5;\r\n	}\r\n	echo $x;// 10\r\n5.How to make local variables to global.\r\nUse static keyword.\r\nfunction myTest() {\r\n    static $x = 0;\r\n    echo $x; \r\n    $x++;\r\n }\r\nmyTest();    //0\r\nmyTest();   //1\r\nmyTest();  //2\r\n ','','4'),
