(1,'Template Files','header.php //for generating the site’s header\r\nfooter.php //for generating the footer\r\nsidebar.php //for generating the sidebar\r\nindex.php //main file\r\nstyle.css //all styles and header info of theme\r\nrtl.css //right to left text direction\r\ncomments.php\r\nfront-page.php\r\nhome.php // If not  use a static front page, this template is used to show latest posts\r\nheader.php //header info meta title, etc\r\nsingular.php //us when single.php !=>page.php If singular.php is not found, index.php is used.\r\nsingle.php //for single post\r\nsingle-{post-type}.php // for single post with custom type ie single-book.php for type post book. if not found index.php used\r\narchive-{post-type}.php //post type archive ,archive.php used if archive-{post-type}.php not found\r\npage.php //all pages follow this file\r\npage-{slug}.php //ie page-about.php\r\ncategory.php //when visitors request posts by category.\r\ntag.php //when visitors request posts by tag.\r\ntaxonomy.php //when a visitor requests a term in a custom taxonomy.\r\nauthor.php\r\ndate.php //The date/time template is used when posts are requested by date or time.\r\nsearch.php //display a visitor’s search results.\r\nattachment.php //single image, file etc\r\n404.php //\r\nimage.php //for image if image.php not  found attachement.php used\r\n\r\nUSE TEMPLATE FILE\r\nget_header() //header.php\r\nget_sidebar() //\r\nget_footer() //footer.php\r\nget_search_form() //search.php\r\nget_template_part(\'my\');//my.php\r\nget_header( \'custom_h\' ); //custom_h.php\r\n','WordPress themes are made up of template files. These are PHP files that contain a mixture of HTML, Template Tags, and PHP code.\r\n1.Make any template File ie search.php in themes/yourTheme/search.php\r\n2.call function ie get_search_form(); in themes/yourTheme/index.php\r\n3.Get Result','template'),
(2,'style.css','######## Style.css ########\r\n/*\r\nTheme Name: Twenty Seventeen\r\nTheme URI: https://wordpress.org/themes/twentyseventeen/\r\nAuthor: the WordPress team\r\nAuthor URI: https://wordpress.org/\r\nDescription: Twenty Seventeen brings your site to life with immersive featured images and subtle animations. With a focus on business sites, it features multiple sections on the front page as well as widgets, navigation and social menus, a logo, and more. Personalize its asymmetrical grid with a custom color scheme and showcase your multimedia content with post formats. Our default theme for 2017 works great in many languages, for any abilities, and on any device.\r\nVersion: 1.0\r\nLicense: GNU General Public License v2 or later\r\nLicense URI: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html\r\nText Domain: twentyseventeen\r\nTags: one-column, two-columns, right-sidebar, flexible-header, accessibility-ready, custom-colors, custom-header, custom-menu, custom-logo, editor-style, featured-images, footer-widgets, post-formats, rtl-language-support, sticky-post, theme-options, threaded-comments, translation-ready\r\nThis theme, like WordPress, is licensed under the GPL.\r\nUse it to make something cool, have fun, and share what you\'ve learned with others.\r\n*/\r\nbody {\r\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\r\n    font-size: 16px;\r\n}\r\n\r\n######## functions.php ########\r\nfunction custom_theme_assets() {\r\n	wp_enqueue_style( \'style\', get_stylesheet_uri() );\r\n}\r\nadd_action( \'wp_enqueue_scripts\', \'custom_theme_assets\' );\r\n','It controls the presentation (visual design and layout) of the website pages.\r\n1.Make style.css in themes/your/style.css\r\n2.make themes/your/function.php\r\n','style'),
(3,'POST TYPES','','Stored in wp_posts->post_type\r\n1.\r\nPost (Post Type: ‘post’);// used for blog, {single, single-post, category, tag, taxonomy, archive, author, date.php, search, \r\nhome,\r\nindex}.php template files used\r\n2.\r\nPage (Post Type: ‘page’). {page, $custom, front-page, search, index}.php templates used\r\n3.\r\nAttachment (Post Type: ‘attachment’) {MIME_type.php, attachment.php, single-attachment.php, single.php ,index.php}\r\n4.\r\nRevision (Post Type: ‘revision’);\r\n5.\r\nNavigation menu (Post Type: ‘nav_menu_item’);\r\n','postTypes'),
(4,'Organizing Theme Files','assets (dir)\r\n      - css (dir)\r\n      - images (dir)\r\n      - js (dir)\r\ninc (dir)\r\ntemplate-parts (dir)\r\n      - footer (dir)\r\n      - header (dir)\r\n      - navigation (dir)\r\n      - page (dir)\r\n      - post (dir)\r\n404.php\r\narchive.php\r\ncomments.php\r\nfooter.php\r\nfront-page.php\r\nfunctions.php\r\nheader.php\r\nindex.php\r\npage.php\r\nREADME.txt\r\nrtl.css\r\nscreenshot.png\r\nsearch.php\r\nsearchform.php\r\nsidebar.php\r\nsingle.php\r\nstyle.css\r\n','',''),
(5,'Templete Hirarchy (which page shown if not found then what)','Left to right use following page if not found use next up to index.php','<img src=\"../assets/wph.png\">',''),
